On June 21, 2018, the President signed four laws into effect. The first law, H.R. 1900, designates a museum in Columbus, Ohio, as the National Veterans Memorial and Museum. The second law, H.R. 2333, increases the amount of leverage available to a Small Business Investment Company from $150 million to $175 million. The third law, H.R. 2772, prohibits the Department of Veterans Affairs from reassigning a member of the Senior Executive Service to a similar position within the Department without the written approval of the Secretary. Lastly, H.R. 4743 enhances the Small Business Administration's oversight authorities of its small business guaranteed lending program, the 7(a) loan program.